article.description: Eddie Stansberry made six 3-pointers and finished with 26 points -- both career highs -- to help Hawaii beat Alabama A&M 71-63 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Stansberry hits 6 3s, scores 26; Hawaii beats Alabama A&M
article.linkText: Stansberry hits 6 3s, scores 26; Hawaii beats Alabama A&M
article.story: HONOLULU -- Eddie Stansberry made six 3-pointers and finished with 26 points -- both career highs -- to help Hawaii beat Alabama A&M 71-63 on Saturday night. Zigmars Raimo had 14 points and seven rebounds and Jack Purchase added nine points, eight boards and four assists for Hawaii. The Rainbow Warriors (9-6) have won three in row. Raimo made a layup, hit a jumper and then took a steal coast-to-coast for a dunk to spark a 16-5 run that made it 59-48 with nine minutes left after Sheriff Drammeh made back-to-back 3-pointers. Tre Todd scored five points during a 9-0 spurt that trimmed Alabama A&M's deficit to 63-61 with 1:53 to play but Stansberry answered with a 3-point play and the Bulldogs got no closer. Todd -- a 5-foot-11, 155-pound juco transfer -- hit four 3s and finished with 18 points, both career highs, for Alabama A&M (1-12). The Bulldogs finished with a season-high 10 3-pointers, but made just 2 of 12 in the second half.
